{
  "texts": [
    "Existing controlled vocabularies and ontologies may lack the necessary granularity to capture the full range of sample origins.",
    "Inflexible Ontology Relationships: Some databases rely on hierarchical ontology relationships, which can be inflexible and may not accommodate the complexity and diversity of environmental descriptions adequately (Romano et al., 2011).",
    "The limitations of existing metagenome databases primarily revolve around the challenges related to metadata quality, standardization, and accessibility.",
    "These limitations hinder the full potential of metagenomic data analysis and the ability to perform comprehensive cross-study comparisons and metaanalyses.",
    "The development of automated methods for metadata extraction and more user-friendly interfaces is essential to address these limitations and unlock the full value of metagenomic datasets."
  ]
}